    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\n`vim.pos` and `vim.range` don't accept `0` for \"current buffer\" like other interfaces.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nAccept `0` to mean \"current buffer\" in `vim.pos` and `vim.range`\r\n\r\nAddresses \"support buf=0 to mean \"current buffer\"? vim.pos(0), :extmark(0,...), etc. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38665#discussion_r3040287364\" from https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38561",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-26T10:34:18Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think it's best to keep `buf` as the last argument, so that it can be made optional and default to `0`.",
