            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "An advantage of having `buf` as the first argument is that it's possible to do something like\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal node = vim.treesitter.get_node()\r\nlocal range = vim.range(0, node:range())\r\n```",
