        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "That makes sense, but the situation mentioned above would be more convenient if it were the last optional argument and defaulted to 0:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal node = vim.treesitter.get_node()\r\nlocal range = vim.range(node:range())\r\n```\r\nThe issue with it is likely that it cannot accept arguments other than 0, for example like this\r\n```lua\r\nlocal node = vim.treesitter.get_node()\r\nlocal range = vim.range(node:range(), 3) --- wrong, receive `row`, `buf`, col is discharged\r\n```",
            "created_at": "2026-04-26T02:57:16Z",
